
[1]intimately

   IN'TIMATELY, adv. Closely; with close intermixture and union of parts;
   as two fluids intimately mixed.

   1. Closely; with nearness of friendship or alliance; as two friends
   intimately united; two families intimately connected.

   2. Familiarly; particularly; as, to be intimately acquainted with facts
   or with a subject.
